  {"original_name":"Nesting Sites suitability","category":"Biodiversity & ecosystems","sub_category":"pollinator habitat suitability","short_description":"Total suitability index for wild bee nesting across all guilds","TNFD_link":"LEAP-L (Locate) & LEAP-E (Evaluate): identify and assess nesting habitat quality for pollinators; Dependency & Impact disclosure","TNFD_metric_type":"ecosystem condition \u2013 pollinator habitat","TNFD_code":"C5.0","SBTN_link":"Realm: Land; Steps: Assess, Act; Pressure: habitat loss; metric: nesting habitat area","CSRD_ESRS_link":"ESRS E4-5 (ecosystem services, species habitat); ESRS E4-2 (restoration targets)","India_relevance":"high","India_notes":"Nesting substrates vary by Indian ecozone: agro-forestry soils in Indo-Gangetic Plain vs laterite soils in Western Ghats. Combine ISRO soil maps, NBSAP habitat assessments.","Darukaa_status":"prototype","input_data_required":"soil type map, LULC, vegetation density, DEM, wetland map","open_data_sources":["ISRO LULC Bhuvan","FAO HWSD soil database","NBSAP habitat data","ESA WorldCover","GBIF bee occurrences India"],"access_type":"mixed","computation_complexity":"medium","example_use_case":"A renewable energy developer assesses nesting habitat suitability before siting solar panels to minimise impacts on wild bee communities and documents this in TNFD Locate disclosures."},
